A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Part 1 of Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia
2 Annotated, relating to the Board of Regents, so as to provide that the Board of Regents shall
3 include members who are graduates of a historically black college or university that is a unit
4 of the University System of Georgia; to provide for a definition; to provide for related
5 matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Part 1 of Article 2 of Chapter 3 of Title 20 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
9 relating to the Board of Regents, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as
10 follows:
11 "20-3-21.1.
12 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'historically black college or university' means
13 an institution that meets the eligibility requirements of 34 C.F.R. Section 608.2 as of
14 January 1, 2025, and which is a unit of the University System of Georgia.
15 (b)(1) Beginning January 1, 2028, at least one at-large member of the board shall be a
16 graduate of a historically black college or university.
